  {
    "id": "a5533434-4ac7-4b8d-a3e1-c4b8004716d7",
    "sentence": "The originate-to-distribute model of mortgage lending on its face promised a social-welfare-enhancing distribution of mortgage credit risk away from banks and toward stable capital market investors.",
    "source": "Financial Institutions, Financial Markets, and Financial Stability",
    "doc_type": "speech",
