    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "73b3251a-da0f-4041-94b8-9d2ce81c855a",
    "sentence": "By comparison, in September 2012, the central tendency of estimates of the longer-run unemployment rate ranged from 5.2 to 6.0 percent.",
    "source": "Economic Outlook and Monetary Policy",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2015-10-12",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a76cced7-1cac-42df-a122-952fc6213850",
    "sentence": "One possibility is that new technologies, by lowering the barriers to workforce entry, could raise employment and labor force participation.",
    "source": "The \"Gig\" Economy: Implications of the Growth of Contingent Work",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2016-11-17",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "5c7e4c36-250c-4181-877f-3179c0140caf",
    "sentence": "Monetary Policy\r\nWhile liquidity provision and other emergency steps were critical to stemming the financial panic, a rapid shift in the stance of monetary policy was necessary to counteract the massive economic blow delivered by the crisis.",
    "source": "The Federal Reserve:  Looking Back, Looking Forward",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2014-01-03",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "2e6164f5-10b4-4354-acd9-1106a3412839",
    "sentence": "Inflation is being restrained by the continued slack in labor and product markets, while stable inflation expectations have offset disinflationary pressures to some extent.",
    "source": "Prospects for a Stronger Recovery",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2013-05-16",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f02d4493-3766-4d21-a511-a25273fc194d",
    "sentence": "Economic history and recent research have sharpened some of the questions, even if they have not produced the easy policy narratives we might prefer. What is clear is that policy decisions taken under uncertainty may look quite different from those that would be optimal under certainty, and properly so.",
    "source": "Elevated Economic Uncertainty: Causes and Consequences",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2023-11-14",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e93f9f37-1d11-4a1b-aeb2-b6fc81eea814",
    "sentence": "However, substantial cross-country evidence suggests that, in low-inflation environments, inflation is notably less responsive to downward pressure from labor market slack than it is when inflation is elevated.",
    "source": "Perspectives on Monetary Policy",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2012-06-06",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "b7603abe-19c3-4953-b8cd-cde5eabb4a16",
    "sentence": "Some are considering how long to keep rates at restrictive levels or, if inflation picks up again, whether to raise rates further.",
    "source": "Common Inflation and Monetary Policy Challenges across Countries",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2024-07-10",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "527bb0d7-2072-4d44-9dbc-f0b2e29fd96b",
    "sentence": "The triennial SCF marks its 30th anniversary this year, as the fieldwork for the 2013 survey begins this month.",
    "source": "Aspects of Inequality in the Recent Business Cycle",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2013-04-18",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "22294213-4fe6-4984-8cf2-0c8c784b87ca",
    "sentence": "Substantial progress has been made toward the Federal Reserve's economic objectives of maximum employment and price stability, in putting in place a regulatory and supervisory structure that is well designed to lower the risks to financial stability, and in actually achieving a stronger financial system.",
    "source": "Financial Stability a Decade after the Onset of the Crisis",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2017-08-25",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e7b78390-2f00-4377-afad-b143204977eb",
    "sentence": "Outlook and Monetary Policy\r\nCongress assigned the Federal Reserve the job of promoting maximum employment and price stability. I am pleased to say that our economy is now close to both of those objectives.",
    "source": "The Federal Reserve's Framework for Monitoring Financial Stability",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2018-11-28",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "32808189-4f8c-419a-9716-d33018d1fd4b",
    "sentence": "When the price of any product moves sharply, the economist's first instinct is to look for changes in the supply of or demand for that product.",
    "source": "The U.S. Economic Outlook",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2011-06-07",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "fe731ef9-605b-4892-9d1b-a489f3e7ba65",
    "sentence": "Homeownership has also helped many families build wealth, and accumulated home equity may serve as a financial reserve that can be tapped as needed at a lower cost than most other forms of credit.",
    "source": "The Subprime Mortgage Market",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2007-05-17",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "7579f316-2dec-4cc2-8b6a-5423859c0bda",
    "sentence": "Even so, the cooling in labor market conditions is unmistakable.",
    "source": "Review and Outlook",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2024-08-23",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
