    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "3628da85-8c1a-4e1c-85d4-d28e0428b746",
    "sentence": "And, together, we will ensure that the payments ecosystem continues to move forward for the benefit of households and businesses.",
    "source": "What Roles Should the Private Sector and the Federal Reserve Play in Payments?",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2024-11-12",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "14dc4ceb-dcbd-4a14-9b83-70fac538fd73",
    "sentence": "Given the dissatisfaction with that approach, the Reserve Bank's mandate was refined significantly in 1997, namely, in seeking to keep inflation within the band, the Reserve Bank should avoid \"unnecessary instability\" in output, interest rates, and the exchange rate (Sherwin, 1999).",
    "source": "Comfort Zones, Shmumfort Zones",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2008-03-27",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "46ba42f3-3fb6-4585-861d-0923ac3933d7",
    "sentence": "This last result is similar to one in recent work by my Fed colleagues Ricardo Correa, Horacio Sapriza, and Andrei Zlate.",
    "source": "Dollar Funding and Global Banks",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2012-12-17",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "296473b6-c7cd-4cb2-8d85-6f4eb0d9d8be",
    "sentence": "As you know, the Federal Reserve responded forcefully to the financial crisis by employing a range of measures and programs to provide badly needed liquidity to financial institutions and markets.",
    "source": "The Economic Outlook",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2011-01-07",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f3d5ff20-84b1-45a7-bfc1-778214b995bc",
    "sentence": "It hypothesized a deep recession in the United States, with GDP contracting sharply, unemployment reaching a peak of more than 13 percent, equity prices falling by half, and house prices declining by an additional 20 percent from their 2011 levels.",
    "source": "Developing Tools for Dynamic Capital Supervision",
    "doc_type": "speech",
