    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "sen": "",
    "ten": "",
    "hor": "",
    "com": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "a00c281f-1ec5-4b11-84f5-5162210cfde2",
    "sentence": "Although, in principle, the ability to pay interest on reserves should be sufficient to allow the Federal Reserve to raise interest rates and control money growth, this approach is likely to be more effective if combined with steps to reduce excess reserves.",
    "source": "The Federal Reserve's Balance Sheet: An Update",
    "doc_type": "speech",
