  },
  {
    "id": "1499f0b2-8f00-432e-88d7-50e08a2a53ff",
    "sentence": "Regarding the maximum-employment leg of the dual mandate, the previous statement's discussion of minimizing \"deviations\" of employment from its maximum level does not adequately reflect how the FOMC has actually conducted monetary policy in recent yearsâbefore the pandemicâas the actual unemployment rate was declining and, for several years, remained below SEP median projections of u* (although, to be sure, the earlier statement did acknowledge that it can be difficult to estimate the maximum level of employment with precision).21",
