  {
    "id": "ac6876d7-a9e0-4a19-89a5-3c348ae1f769",
    "sentence": "Of course, an alternative strategy--one consistent with classical principles of international adjustment--is to refrain from intervening in foreign exchange markets, thereby allowing the currency to rise and helping insulate the financial system from external pressures.",
    "source": "U.S. Monetary Policy and International Implications",
    "doc_type": "speech",
