    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "e74c203f-760b-46a9-9de6-32592bc9e2d9",
    "sentence": "As all that happens, the policy easing the Federal Reserve has put in place over recent months will begin to show through more in reductions in the cost of capital and the greater availability of credit.",
    "source": "The Economic Outlook",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2008-05-20",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "c40926e0-2d0e-45f3-bca7-d91a17c2a8c7",
    "sentence": "Using the same estimates for TFP as I used earlier, this suggests 0.2 to 0.6 percentage point of downward pressure on the output gap over the next couple of years.",
    "source": "Nonmonetary Forces and Appropriate Monetary Policy",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2025-09-22",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "363c2de0-36c1-4ff4-9bba-f1d149b11dca",
    "sentence": "Some observers expressed concern at the time that these policies would stoke inflation, and, indeed, inflation reached high levels earlier this year, mostly as the result of a surge in the prices of oil and other commodities.",
    "source": "Federal Reserve Policies in the Financial Crisis",
    "doc_type": "speech",
