    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "775af2e2-9220-438c-a548-ae6263c46109",
    "sentence": "I also know that the U.S. economy has proven itself over the years to be flexible and resilient as well as innovative and productive, qualities which enable it to rebound from serious economic shocks.",
    "source": "Economic Outlook",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2008-10-15",
    "context_question": null,
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "ed838d09-5989-4e02-95e2-aba227d25dc8",
    "sentence": "And ultimately, as you know, it is easier to fix a problem during the good times.",
    "source": "Community Bankers and Supervisors: Seeking Balance",
    "doc_type": "speech",
    "date": "2011-04-07",
    "context_question": null,
